# 06 — Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
## Smart City Network Visualization Platform (SCNVP)
### Version 1.0 | 4-Month MVP Scope

---

## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose
This SRS defines functional and non-functional requirements for SCNVP — a web-based platform for designing, simulating, and managing city-scale network infrastructure, with AI assistance built in.

### 1.2 Scope
SCNVP v1.0 (MVP) covers:
- Web application (React, desktop-first)
- RESTful + WebSocket API (NestJS)
- Network simulation engine (Python/FastAPI)
- AI assistant service (FastAPI/LangChain)
- Deployment: single-region, containerized

### 1.3 Definitions
| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| Node | A network device placed on the canvas |
| Connection/Edge | A link between two nodes |
| Topology | The complete set of nodes and connections in a project |
| Simulation | A computational model run against a topology |
| CAPEX | Capital Expenditure (one-time hardware/installation costs) |
| OPEX | Operational Expenditure (recurring costs) |
| SPOF | Single Point of Failure |

