## 3. Non-Functional Requirements

### NFR-PERF: Performance

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| NFR-PERF-01 | API response time: < 200ms for CRUD operations (p95) |
| NFR-PERF-02 | Canvas rendering: 60fps with up to 500 nodes |
| NFR-PERF-03 | AI first-token response: < 3 seconds |
| NFR-PERF-04 | Simulation start-to-first-metric: < 2 seconds |
| NFR-PERF-05 | Page load (First Contentful Paint): < 2 seconds |

### NFR-SEC: Security

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| NFR-SEC-01 | All API endpoints must require authentication (except auth routes) |
| NFR-SEC-02 | JWT tokens must be validated on every request |
| NFR-SEC-03 | All user inputs must be validated and sanitized |
| NFR-SEC-04 | HTTPS enforced in production |
| NFR-SEC-05 | CORS restricted to known origins |
| NFR-SEC-06 | Rate limiting: 100 req/min per IP globally; per-role AI limits |
| NFR-SEC-07 | No sensitive data (passwords, secrets) in logs |

### NFR-REL: Reliability

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| NFR-REL-01 | API uptime target: 99.5% (MVP) |
| NFR-REL-02 | Auto-save must not lose more than 30 seconds of canvas work |
| NFR-REL-03 | Simulation service failure must not crash main API |
| NFR-REL-04 | AI service failure must show graceful error, not crash canvas |

### NFR-SCALE: Scalability

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| NFR-SCALE-01 | Architecture must support horizontal scaling (stateless API) |
| NFR-SCALE-02 | Database must support up to 10,000 projects without schema changes |
| NFR-SCALE-03 | WebSocket must support 200 concurrent connected clients (MVP) |

### NFR-UX: User Experience

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| NFR-UX-01 | All forms must show validation errors inline |
| NFR-UX-02 | All async operations must show loading state |
| NFR-UX-03 | All destructive actions must require confirmation |
| NFR-UX-04 | Canvas must have keyboard shortcuts: Del, Ctrl+Z, Ctrl+Y, Ctrl+S |
| NFR-UX-05 | Responsive design: functional on 1280px+ screens |

